column1: #  our catalog. With the growth of the network and catalog
#  review has become more difficult with our limited staff. This is
#  particularly true of the 2019 Ridgecrest sequence
#  unreviewed below M2.5.
#  Below we provide information about the review status of the SCSN local event
#  catalog. We hope our catalog users will find this additional context useful.
#  Finalized events have undergone full review and analysis and are unlikely to
#  change. Subnet triggers are collections of phase picks that the real-time
#  system could not associate into an event. Some of the triggers may be events
#  that are later added to the catalog
column2: although most are just noise. Lastly

column1: #  events are sometimes added to the catalog as part of the review process
#  the total number of events can increase.
#  catalog_date:       The day in UTC time which events occurred.
#  pct_complete:       Finalized events/(finalized + unreviewed + partial reviewed events) as %
#                        NaN in this column means there were no events in this day.
#  unreviewed:         Number of real time detected events that have not gone through any review
#  incomplete:         Number of events that have gone through partial review
#  subtrig_cnt:        Number of subnet triggers
#  max_unreviewed_mag: Highest magnitude of unreviewed event on this day in the catalog
